Title: Webinar | Building and Managing Teams for SMEs
Description:
This webinar delves into essential strategies and best practices for effectively building and managing teams to drive business growth and success, particularly focusing on small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). 

Key topics covered includes:
-Essentials of Team Building: Understanding the foundational elements necessary for building strong and cohesive teams within SMEs.

-Hiring the Right Talent: Exploring strategies for recruiting and selecting the right talent that aligns with the organization's goals and culture.

-Nurturing Positive Team Culture: Discussing methods to foster a positive and inclusive team culture that promotes collaboration and innovation.

-Managing and Motivating Teams: Strategies for effective team management, including motivation techniques to drive high-performance and productivity.

-Tools for Efficient Collaboration: Introducing tools and technologies that facilitate efficient collaboration among team members, enhancing productivity and communication within SMEs.

Participants gained insights into actionable strategies and tools to enhance team dynamics, improve productivity, and achieve business success within the SME sector.

Our newly launched product "Cloudenly" was also introduced.

Title: How To Add Your Gateway Control Device To Your EyeSyte System
Description:
Looking to add your Gateway Control Device to your EyeSyte system? Here's a simple step-by-step guide to help you get started:

-Make sure your Gateway Control device is connected to a power source and powered on.

-Log in to your eyesyte account on your computer or mobile device.

-Go to the Devices tab and click on the Add Device button.

-Select Gateway Control from the list of device types and follow the on-screen instructions to complete the setup process.

- Enter the wifi password provided with your Gateway Control device.

- Wait for the device to be recognized by your eyesyte system and fully configured.

- Congratulations, your Gateway Control device is now successfully added to your eyesyte system and ready to use!

By following these simple steps, you'll be able to easily add your Gateway Control device to your eyesyte system and enjoy the benefits of a smarter, more connected home.

Title: MTN ASAP Advocacy Walk | Abuja
Description:
The Anti-Substance Abuse Program (ASAP) is an advocacy campaign designed to reduce the rate of first-time abuse of drugs and other substances among Nigerian youths between the ages of 10 and 25. 

The MTN Foundation partners with the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA), United Nations Office on Drugs & Crime (UNODC) and other relevant agencies to commemorate the International Day Against Drug Abuse and Illicit Trafficking (World Drug Day) every year. 

In view of this, this year‚Äôs Advocacy Walk on anti-substance abuse and a National Conference were held in Abuja in June 2022.  

The MTN Foundation with its partners also held ASAP Quiz Competition for secondary schools‚Äô students in Nigeria, and trained teachers to provide knowledge on substance prevention and dangers of substance abuse among students.

#MTNASAP
Caption: false

‚Ä¢ Enter your Broadband Router phone number and click on ‚ÄòProceed‚Äô, then select ‚ÄòOTP Option‚Äô to choose how you want to receive your OTP (One Time Password)

‚Ä¢ An OTP will be sent either to your alternate phone number or email address, which you provided during the SIM registration of your Broadband Router

‚Ä¢ If you did not provide an alternate contact number or email during SIM registration, note the following:

‚Ä¢ You are required to visit the nearest MTN Store/SIM Registration Centre to update your information on your Broadband Router account for ease of future bundle re-subscriptions

‚Ä¢ Until you update your SIM registration, the OTP will be sent to your Broadband Router router

‚Ä¢ In the case above, you will be required to log into your Broadband Router to fetch the OTP and log into the MTN Data portal on your phone for Broadband Router bundle re-subscription

‚Ä¢ Enter your OTP and click on ‚ÄòProceed.‚Äô

‚Ä¢ You can load airtime into your Broadband Router account from the Voucher ‚ÄòCard section.‚Äô

‚Ä¢ Click on ‚ÄòBundles‚Äô and select ‚ÄòBroadband Router Bundles‚Äô under ‚ÄòBuy Bundles‚Äô

‚Ä¢ Choose a Broadband Router data bundle you want and click on ‚ÄòProceed‚Äô to subscribe

Title: How to Change Broadband Router (HyNetFlex) Hotspot Name and Password
Description:
Gotten your broadband router and need to secure your device?

See below for steps to change your broadband hotspot name (SSID) and Password (WLAN Key) in five (5) easy steps.

Step 1: Connect your Broadband router via Wi-Fi or LAN Cable

Step 2: Open your web browser and type in 192.168.0.1 in the address bar and click ‚Äúenter‚Äù 

Step 3: A login page will open up. In the empty space, type ‚Äúadmin‚Äù as the password and click proceed. 

Step 4: When the interface opens, click on Wi-Fi settings to change the default network name and password respectively to those of your choosing. 
Remember to use a strong and easy to remember password to keep your data extra secure.

Step 5: Click apply and save your new settings!

And Voil√†. You're set to enjoy super-fast, affordable, and uninterrupted internet that's fully secure.

For more details, call the broadband service helpline on 217 or visit www.mtn.ng/broadband

Title: MTN Donates Oligosynthesiser to the Nigerian Institute of Medical Research (NIMR )
Description:
In response to the COVID-19 pandemic and as MTN Nigeria‚Äôs contributions to strengthening the health system particularly research institutions, we have collaborated with the Nigerian Institute of Medical Research in establishing an Oligosynthesiser laboratory. The Oligo-Synthesizer is an equipment that allows for the local development of primers for the indigenous production of test kits for COVID-19 and other outbreak diseases. 

The commissioning of the landmark laboratory took place on Friday, August 13th, 2021 at the NIMR Auditorium, 6, Edmund Crescent, Yaba, Lagos State

When your village is connected to the global village, you go.

When 30 million people have a bank in their pocket, they go.

When 560 million of us can plug into a high-speed digital highway, we go.

When you can use technology to teach, where books can't reach, we all go.

When you're driven by the unstoppable spirit of Africa, you go.

They say if you want to go fast, go alone.

We're good together.

Title: Have you called her today?  My Wonder Woman!
Description:
You are Superwoman, you save the world time and time again. 
You put out fires with your bare hands. 
You end riots immediately with your X-Ray vision stare. 
You feed a whole tribe from one tiny pot, and still find time to manage other nations. 
You give all generations peace with the sound of your voice.  

You never really sleep, you're too busy making sure we're okay and when the sun comes up back in the sky, it finds you at work asking it why it took so long.

Thank you for showing us what TRUE LOVE really means.

Have you called her today?

Title: MTN Nigeria Foundation/MUSON Music Scholars
Description:
Every year, the MTN Nigeria Foundation in partnership with the Musical Society of Nigeria (MUSON) provides 2-year music scholarships to talented Nigerian students to enable them acquire qualitative music education.

So far, 103 students have obtained the prestigious MUSON Diploma in Music. In September 2011, a new batch of 30 students were admitted to MUSON School and  they held an appreciation concert for MTN and the MTN Foundation on December 5, 2011. 

Here is a short video from the event. We thank these worthy music scholars and wish them all the best in their studies!
Caption: false
